  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Although \"Comunidad, pertenencia, extrenjería\" has not generated formal citations or online discussions as of yet, it appears to have established a strong commercial linkage, being available on platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, suggesting a degree of interest within the public domain.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published by Leuven University Press in 2022, \"Comunidad, pertenencia, extrenjería\" explores themes of community, belonging, and foreignness. As of October 2023, the book has not received any recorded citations or online mentions, highlighting a potential gap between academic reception and public engagement. Nevertheless, its presence on commercial platforms, such as Amazon and Goodreads, indicates a potentially interested readership that extends beyond strictly academic circles, suggesting that there might be an emerging discussion yet to fully materialize.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The inferred data signals reflect a significant commercial linkage, scoring 0.9. This high score underscores the book's potential appeal and accessibility to a broader audience. Additionally, the work has a moderate relevance to sustainability and policy, indicated by its connection to one Sustainable Development Goal (SDG), which hints at its applicability to contemporary societal issues.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of formal scholarly uptake as seen through the lack of citations, the book’s content could serve as a foundational resource within the discourse surrounding community and identity. The lack of any high-fidelity community discourse on platforms like Wikipedia, Reddit, or Bluesky may indicate an opportunity for growth and future engagement, inviting scholars and the public alike to consider its implications in an increasingly interconnected world.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Future analysis may focus on tracking how this work evolves in its impact and relevance within the context of ongoing discussions around community and identity. The groundwork laid by this publication could serve to inspire further research and dialogue as its themes continue to resonate with readers and researchers in the field.</p>",
